The genus is widely distributed worldwide, with 204 valid species, 22 of which have been recorded from China (
Zhang and Huang 2007
). Most species of the genus are parasitic on lepidopteran insects, especially endoparasitic in eggs and larvae (
Noyes 2019
), which provide good prevention and control effects on agriculture and forestry pest populations.

